  "text": "The Itô integrals with respect to G-Lévy processes. In the subsection, we introduce the Itô integrals with respect to G-Lévy processes under the framework of the above subsection. Let X denote the canonical process on the space, i.e. X t (ω) = ω t , t ∈ [0, T ]. So, X is a d-dimensional G-Lévy process. Although the Itô integrals with respect to G-Brownian motions have been introduced in [CITATION_1] , we need to introduce two related spaces used in the sequel. Take Next, we introduce the Itô integrals with respect to random measures. First, define a random measure: for any 0 t T and A ∈ B(R d \\ {0}),",
